registry.title: YANG Module Names
registry.note: YANG modules are additionally available for bulk retrieval by Rsync (rsync.iana.org::assignments/yang-parameters/) or FTP (ftp://ftp.iana.org/assignments/yang-parameters/).

record.name: iana-bfd-types
record.notes: BFD Diagnostic Codes and BFD Authentication Types must not be added directly to the iana-bfd-types YANG module. They must first be added to , which it mirrors.

record.name: iana-bgp-l2-encaps
record.notes: BGP Layer 2 encapsulation types must not be directly added to the "iana-bgp-l2-encaps" YANG module. They must instead be added to the "BGP Layer 2 Encapsulation Types" registry at .

record.name: iana-crypt-hash
record.notes: Registration procedure: Expert Review, as described in . Expert(s): Kent Watsen.

record.name: iana-dns-class-rr-type
record.notes: Classes and types of DNS resource records must not be directly added to the "iana-dns-class-rr-type" YANG module. They must instead be added to the "DNS CLASSes" and "Resource Record (RR) TYPEs" registries, respectively.

record.name: iana-dots-signal-channel
record.notes: Status, conflict status, conflict cause, and attack status values must not be directly added to the iana-dots-signal-channel YANG module. They must instead be respectively added to the "DOTS Status Codes", "DOTS Conflict Status Codes", "DOTS Conflict Cause Codes", and "DOTS Attack Status Codes" registries.

record.name: iana-hardware
record.notes: The "iana-hardware" YANG module is intended to reflect the "IANA-ENTITY-MIB" MIB module so that if a new enumeration is added to the "IANAPhysicalClass" textual convention, the same class is added as an identity derived from "ianahw:hardware-class".

record.name: iana-if-type
record.notes: Interface types must not be directly added to the iana-if-type YANG module. They must instead be added to the "Interface Types (ifType)" registry at .

record.name: iana-pseudowire-types
record.notes: MPLS pseudowire types must not be directly added to the "iana-pseudowire-types" YANG module. They must instead be added to the "MPLS Pseudowire Types" registry at .

record.name: iana-routing-types
record.notes: Address Families and Subsequent Address Families must not be directly added to the iana-routing-types YANG module. They must instead be respectively added to the Address Family Numbers and Subsequent Address Family Identifiers (SAFI) Parameters registries.

record.name: iana-tunnel-type
record.notes: Tunnel type values must not be directly added to the iana-tunnel-type YANG module. They must instead be added to the "Tunnel Types (tunnelType)" subregistry (under the "Interface Types (ifType)" registry) at .
